ertain rectangular area with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a specific aspect ratio: the region or rectangle of interest. This is where a view finder comes in.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It crops the video frame to that region of interest before passing it to any scanner. Usually","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the performance of scanners gain a benefit from it because less pixels must be processed.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Additionally, to guide the user, the view finder visualizes the region of interest by drawing a rectangle around","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on the user interface.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SBSDKBaseScannerViewFinderConfiguration","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"SBSDKBaseScannerViewFinderConfiguration","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkbasescannerviewfinderconfiguration","role":"symbol"},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK/SBSDKBaseScannerViewFinderConfiguration/secondaryAspectRatio":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"secondaryAspectRatio"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@M@ScanbotSDK@objc(cs)SBSDKAspectRatio","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"SBSDKAspectRatio"},{"kind":"text","text":"?"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"secondaryAspectRatio"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The aspect ratio of the secondary view finder that is displayed with dashed lines.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If set to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" no secondary view finder is drawn."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Defaults to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"title":"secondaryAspectRatio","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/Scan